RabbitMQ doesn't auto-propagate W3C trace context like HTTP does. You need to **manually inject/extract** it via message headers using `System.Diagnostics`.

## Publisher (Service A)

```csharp
using var activity = ActivitySource.StartActivity("OrderPublished", ActivityKind.Producer);

var props = channel.CreateBasicProperties();
props.Headers ??= new Dictionary<string, object>();

// Inject current trace context into message headers
if (Activity.Current != null)
{
    props.Headers["traceparent"] = Activity.Current.Id;
    props.Headers["tracestate"] = Activity.Current.TraceStateString ?? "";
}

channel.BasicPublish(exchange, routingKey, props, body);
```

## Consumer (Service B)

```csharp
var parentContext = default(ActivityContext);

if (ea.BasicProperties.Headers?.TryGetValue("traceparent", out var raw) == true)
{
    var traceparent = Encoding.UTF8.GetString((byte[])raw);
    ActivityContext.TryParse(traceparent, null, out parentContext);
}

// Start a linked activity so it joins the same trace
using var activity = ActivitySource.StartActivity(
    "OrderConsumed",
    ActivityKind.Consumer,
    parentContext   // <-- this is the key link
);
```

## Why it doesn't work today

- HTTP instrumentation auto-injects `traceparent`/`tracestate` headers. RabbitMQ's `BasicPublish` has no such built-in behavior.
- Without passing `parentContext` to `StartActivity`, Service B starts a **new** trace root.

## Cleaner alternative: use `OpenTelemetry.Api` propagator

```csharp
// Shared helper — works with any carrier (headers dict, etc.)
private static readonly TextMapPropagator Propagator = Propagators.DefaultTextMapPropagator;

// INJECT (publisher)
Propagator.Inject(
    new PropagationContext(activity.Context, Baggage.Current),
    props.Headers,
    (headers, key, value) => headers[key] = value);

// EXTRACT (consumer)
var ctx = Propagator.Extract(
    default,
    ea.BasicProperties.Headers,
    (headers, key) =>
    {
        if (headers.TryGetValue(key, out var val))
            return new[] { Encoding.UTF8.GetString((byte[])val) };
        return Enumerable.Empty<string>();
    });

using var activity = ActivitySource.StartActivity(
    "OrderConsumed", ActivityKind.Consumer, ctx.ActivityContext);
```

This approach uses the standard W3C `TextMapPropagator`, handles both `traceparent` and `tracestate`, and works with any OTel exporter (Jaeger, Zipkin, OTLP).

**TL;DR:** Inject `Activity.Current.Id` into `IBasicProperties.Headers` on publish, extract it and pass as `parentContext` to `StartActivity` on consume. That's the missing link.
